# Blit-Tech API names in demos

Demos call the library through `BT` and `configure()` — use the **same public names** as blit-tech.

Canonical references (read before adding or renaming API usage):

- [blit-tech/CLAUDE.md](https://github.com/vancura/blit-tech/blob/main/CLAUDE.md) — **Boolean naming**, **BT API: getters vs methods**, **Input conventions**
- [blit-tech/docs/developer-experience-guide.md](https://github.com/vancura/blit-tech/blob/main/docs/developer-experience-guide.md) — full three-tier boolean table
- [blit-tech/docs/input.md](https://github.com/vancura/blit-tech/blob/main/docs/input.md) — input examples

## Configure flags (Tier B)

Use grammatical `is*` names from `HardwareSettings`:

- `isOverlayEnabled`, `isOverlayVisibleAtStart`, `isOverlayToggleHintVisible`, `isOverlayToggleEnabled`
- `isOverlayPaletteEnabled`, `isOverlayTimingChartEnabled`, `isOverlayRendererDiagnosticsBarEnabled`
- `isDetectingDroppedFrames`, `isWaitingForDOMReady`
- `canvasID`, `containerID` in bootstrap options (not `canvasId`)

## Input on `BT` (Tier A)

- Hold: `BT.isDown(...)`, `BT.isKeyDown(...)`
- Edge: `BT.isPressed(...)`, `BT.isReleased(...)`, `BT.isKeyPressed(...)`, `BT.isKeyReleased(...)`
- Pointer: `BT.isPointerActive(slot?)`

Do not use removed names: `BT.isButtonDown` (use `BT.isDown`), `isKeyIsDown` / `isKeyIsPressed` (embedded `Is`), `overlayEnabled`, `canvasId`.

## When the library API changes

Update affected demo `configure()` blocks, runtime call sites, this repo's `CLAUDE.md`, and `README.md` in the same change.
